				\begin{document}$$Fd\bar{3}m$$\end{document}Fd3¯m, Z = 8, a = 0.9–1.2 nm) and adopt the pyrochlore structure, which is related to ideal fluorite but with ordered cation sites and anion vacancies. If the cation radius ratio is above 1.78, then a monoclinic layered perovskite structure (P21) is favored, while for a ratio below 1.46, a distorted fluorite structure (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
